Sentencas: Novel cathode material Bi1.91Sr2Co1.96O7.08 (BSCO) was synthesized by ethylene glycol assisted sol-gel method for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Preparation and evaluation of novel Bi1.91Sr2Co1.96O7.08 cathode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: In addition to its good thermal stability, it shows chemical and thermal compatibility with Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 gamma electrolyte.
Titulo: Preparation and evaluation of novel Bi1.91Sr2Co1.96O7.08 cathode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Thermal expansion coefficient of BSCO is found to be approximately 11.2 x 10(-6) K-1 from 100 degrees C to 800 degrees C, which is the main merit of this material compared with other cobaltite based perovskite cathodes.
Titulo: Preparation and evaluation of novel Bi1.91Sr2Co1.96O7.08 cathode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Electrical conductivity of BSCO is about 8-9 S cm(-1) between 600 and 700 degrees C, and polarization resistance of BSCO cathode on Ce0.9Gd0.1O2 gamma electrolyte are 0.1, 0.3 and 1.3 Omega.cm(2) at 800, 748 and 695 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: Preparation and evaluation of novel Bi1.91Sr2Co1.96O7.08 cathode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Maximum power density based on BSCO/GDC/NiO-GDC cell is 495 mW.cm(-2) at 700 degrees C.
Titulo: Preparation and evaluation of novel Bi1.91Sr2Co1.96O7.08 cathode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Given that the thermal compatibility with the electrolyte and the encouraging electrochemical performance, BSCO could be considered as an alternative cathode material for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Preparation and evaluation of novel Bi1.91Sr2Co1.96O7.08 cathode for intermediate temperature-solid oxide fuel cells
